-- Enerjisa Lenders Market $972 Billion of Loans to Expand Power Generation
-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s   a n d   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 2010-11-09T11:57:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/enerjisa-seeks-700-million-euros-loan-via-ifc-unicredit-westlb.html
Lenders to  Enerjisa Enerji Uretim AS ,
the Turkish power utility, started marketing 700 million euros
($972 billion) of loans to fund the expansion of its power
generation assets.  The 12-year financing includes a loan for commercial
lenders and a portion that will be held by the International
Finance Corp., according to a statement from arrangers IFC,
UniCredit SpA and WestLB AG. Turkish and multilateral
development banks will be allocated other portions.  The loan is part of a 1 billion-euro financing for the
development of 1,045 mega-watt power generation projects
including gas turbine, hydroelectric power plants and a wind
farm. The remaining 300 million euros will come from equity, the
lenders said.  The IFC is a member of the World Bank Group. Enerjisa is
owned by Austrian power company  Verbund  and  Haci Omer Sabanci
Holding AS .  To contact the reporter on this story:
